eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more details. #DStv403 VEREENIGING - Hundreds of people have been displaced after floods swept through large parts of the Vaal. Scores of homes were submerged underwater after the Rietspruit and Vaal rivers burst their banks. Residents were forced to evacuate while some were rescued by helicopter. READ: Gauteng Floods | Vaal Dam overflows The area flooded after 12 sluice gates at the  Vaal dam were opened to ease rising water levels. The  Emfuleni municipality meanwhile is still nowhere to be seen. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more details in the video above.